reviews.review: It's not a Star Wars movie, it's a marvel movie in a Star Wars skin. But that being said, taking into account the limits set on the writing team and story, it's fine. It's not going to be remembered for any epic scene or moment, it's going to be remembered as the last one that ended the saga, that's it. It was nostalgic and predictable. But.... It's over, and a part of me hates that it is. The force will be with us, always.
This truly is the worst Star Wars movie ever made. I was laughing at how terrible it was. I felt like I was watching a Robot Chicken or SNL  A fan fic would be better.
J.J. Abrams and all the cast made an excellent work. This is an epic movie that deserves to be part of the Star Wars universe. Thank you guys for making a galaxy far far way such an amazing place.
Good visuals and movie feeling, but predictable at times, and in some ways undermined the original 6 movies. There were also too many returns of characters and “I am still alive” moments

One of the best Star Wars movies every. Lots of action with surprises and twists. If you are a Star Wars fan, it tugs at you emotionally, but wraps the saga up well. I saw Star Wars (what would later become A New Hope) in 1977 as a kid. It's my favorite movie of all time.  I put this installment up there with A New Hope and The Empire Strikes Back and I can't wait to see it again.

JJ did a great job telling an entertaining story that completes the trilogy and the saga.  The Last Jedi's epic misfires left JJ with little to work with.  But he did it well.  His efforts actually make some of the things that happened in Last Jedi come across better.  This movie is entertaining as the Star Wars and Empire were. It allows the new characters to work together which is a good thing.  The relationship between the characters in the original trilogy is such an important part of why that trilogy works.  It was absent or forced in the Last Jedi.  It was present in Force Awakens and here those relationships and characters further develop.  Excellent story telling, particularly given the difficult spot the last film left the overall story and franchise.

Seeing people score opposite of critics speaks volumes. JJ had a big task to unf...ck Rian Johnson abomination called TLJ and he did the best he could. The movie is not perfect but was a satisfying conclusion of Skywalker saga.
the worse Star wars movie of them all.

The leaks were all true and this is just a long movie just to confirmed Reylo shipping. Only watch this not for the plot, but if you are just want your ship to be vailded and to finally see a kiss between them. Would not recommend.

Phenomenal effort from J.J. and crew! I loved every minute of it. The movie is not only great but it makes other Saga movies before it better than they already were. Critics will not understand this movie. Star Wars fans will love it.
